All 455 tests pass. Here's a summary of the 3 bugs I fixed in `inflection/__init__.py`:

1. **`camelize` (line 169)**: The `uppercase_first_letter=True` branch called `.lower()` instead of `.upper()`, producing lowercase output when it should have been CamelCase.

2. **`ordinal` (line 229)**: The teen check used `number % 10 in (11, 12, 13)` which is impossible (mod 10 yields 0-9). Fixed to `number % 100 in (11, 12, 13)` to correctly handle 11th, 12th, 13th, 111th, etc.

3. **`PLURALS` y→ies rule (line 29)**: The replacement `r'\1ys'` produced "categorys" instead of "categories". Fixed to `r'\1ies'`.
